args: At this rate, the whole mountain will be\nablaze! I shall fight fire with fire. YAH!
I'll set some smaller fires for a controlled\nburn, and then go around and put out\nthe other fires!
Glad you made it out, Gozu Tenno.\nWhat of Addis?
After you took off, he followed you.\nAre you not with him?
No... Is he still in there?!
Please continue extinguishing the flames.\nI am returning to the workshop.
Don't be absurd! It's a sea of flame!
I'm all too aware of the danger.
Saiga... You came to help me?!
You're pinned beneath a fallen pillar.\nI'm going to move it. One...two...HEAVE!
The fire is getting worse.\nJust get the hell outta here!
No! I'm not done yet.\nI will NOT leave you!
Then we'll just die together, fool!
I would never leave you to die and live on.\nNEVER! HRAAAAAAAH!
I owe you for this, Saiga.
I managed to prevent the fire from\nengulfing the forest. What in the\nworld was that explosion?
It was a bomb that used a jufu talisman\nand oilâ€”one likely set up to dispose of the\nworkshop now that it's fallen into disuse.
I suspect the shadow that aimed a caster\nat us was a Mukuroshu agent who had\ncome to trigger the blast.

I at least grabbed the map we found, but
it's gonna be rough figuring out where they
moved their workshop when this is all
we've got to go on.
A manacaster is loaded with and fires\nblasts of mana. They would need an\nabundant source of it to work with them.
That's it! Look here, you two.

This map shows the location of a
dragon-vein spring in the south of the
continent. Lord Seimei had his shikigami
make it.
If they want to set up a smithy, I wager the\nmost suitable spot for them would be near\na dragon-vein spring and a mine alike.
So geographically speaking,\nthe ideal location would be...
I've arranged a room for you. If you give\nthe inn my name, they'll put you up.
You guys are all going to check out the\nmine tomorrow, right? If there's anything\nyou need, we'll get it ready for you.
By the WAY, Eugeneâ€”I hear you're doing\nthe whole ï¼‚nougat for three meals a dayï¼‚\nthing again. Stop poisoning your body!
Huh? You're bringing that up NOW?\nAnd it's none of your business anyway!
The pair of you are old friends, I see.
Oh, uh... Yeah, I guess we are.
Do you have any childhood friends, Saiga?
What would make you ask that?
When you were looking at Eugene and\nCatherine, I saw a warmth in your eyes.
I...knew my wife Momoyo from a young\nage. They simply reminded me of that.
What kinda woman was Momoyo,\nif you don't mind me asking?
...I was an orphan, and something of a\nrough-and-tumble one at that. Even so,\nshe talked to me without any hesitation.

It was at her recommendation that I joined
her grandfather's dojo. She felt that if I
had something to devote myself to, it
would distract me from my loneliness.
She was a gentle, attentive woman.\nHer kindness saved me.
It sounds as though she was truly precious\nto you.
Indeed. That's why when she died, I lost\nall reason. I could not conceive of a life\nwithout her.

Thus did the Mukuroshu's sweet lies tempt
me like so much honey. And in the end...
I took my teacher'sâ€”Momoyo and
Yachiyo's grandfather'sâ€”life.
Once I'd killed him, I finally realized\nthat the work I was doing was vile.\nI was robbing people of their loved ones.
From that moment forth, I swore to spend\nthe rest of my life atoning for my myriad\nsins.
That's why I will destroy their workshop.\nI will do whatever it takes to ensure that\ntheir weapons spill no new blood.
I am not long for this world. Permit me\nto make a final request of you, Saiga.
Where are you?! MOMOYO!\nSHOW YOURSELF TO ME, PLEASE!
My heart is hammering.\nSleep won't take me again anytime soon.
In that dream... I remembered her words,\nas she lay dying in bed.
Back then, she was trying to tell me toâ€”
You... You're the Mukuroshu agent from\nthe old workshop!

You would preach about your new life?
What sickening indulgence. In the past,
you looked away from reality, and now
you look away from yourself.

More than you ever will. No matter how
desperately you try to atone, the dead will
remain forever that: dead. That you would
live on is presumptuous in the extreme.
Saiga, I wondered where you had gone.\nSo this is where you were.
Beware the Mukuroshu! That agent has\na caster!
What do you mean, ï¼‚where?ï¼‚\nThe enemy is right in frontâ€”
